Usage: lunchtoast <testPath> [params] [flags] 
Arguments:
    <testPath> (path)     a test file or a directory containing tests
Parameters:
   -report=<path>         save test report to file
                            (optional, default: "")
   -ext=<string>          the extension of searched test files, required when 
                            specified test path is a directory
                            (optional, default: .toast)
   -width=<int>           set test report's width in number of characters
                            (optional, default: 48)
   -shell=<string>        shell command
                            (optional, default: sh -c -e)
   -select=<string>       select tests by tag names
                            (multi-value, optional, default: {})
   -skip=<string>         skip tests by tag names
                            (multi-value, optional, default: {})
Flags:
  --saveContents          save the current contents of of the test directory
  --noCleanup             disables cleanup of test files
  --help                  show usage info and exit

